<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="41">-The generic description applies. Bases of hind wings in mature adult dark red, yellow, or orange. Abdominal tergites banded in dark blue.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="41">-Found principally in the African Sahel region, from SENEGAL to CHAD, but also occurs in D.R. CONGO, MALAWI, and UGANDA: Adjumani and W. Busoga.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
- 
<bibRefCitation author="Fishpool, LDC" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut Fondamental d'Afrique Noire" pageId="49" pageNumber="86" pagination="275 - 410" title="The grasshopper faunas of the savannas of Mali, Niger, Benin and Togo." volume="43" year="1984">Fishpool and Popov (1984)</bibRefCitation>
record the species in MALI as being gramnivorous and mesophilous. In 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Uganda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uganda" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Uganda</taxonomicName>
it occurs in dry grass savanna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
